Definition 3.13. Consider the weakest equivalence relation on the set of all Young diagrams such that $\lambda$ and $\mu$ are equivalent whenever the indecomposable object $L(\lambda)$ is a direct summand of $L(\mu)\otimes[pt]$ in $\underline{\operatorname{Re}}\!\operatorname{p}(S_{d})$. When $\lambda$ and $\mu$ are in the same equivalence class we write $\lambda\stackrel{{\scriptstyle d}}{{\approx}}\mu$.
